Post appacalypit, global warming, locusts, ravaging bands of nomads. 
-------------------------------------------------------------------
			After Blast

Heat shimmered up in waves from the blazing red sand. Mark Storm took a parched sip from his water skin and threw the now empty sack angrily onto the hot sands. His dry tounge licked his cracked lips with an automatic wiping motion. In the distance he saw the spear tips of his enemies.

Mark lifted his compact binoculars up to his dry red eyes. They had her. A one weeks march from Lost Vegas. They were comming. 

He curled up behind a rock. Hot stones and sand burned his skin but he mustn't cry out.  
